H0.text: May 15, 1940 saw what fast food chain get started in San Bernadino, CA. In-N-Out Burger

H1.text: May 15, 1940 saw what fast food chain get started in San Bernadino, CA. Del Taco

H2.text: May 15, 1940 saw what fast food chain get started in San Bernadino, CA. Carl's Jr.

H3.text: May 15, 1940 saw what fast food chain get started in San Bernadino, CA. McD

A4.text: The first Del Taco restaurant was opened in Yermo, California, on September 16, 1964.

A5.text: Carl's Jr. was founded in 1941 by Carl Karcher in Los Angeles, starting with a hot dog cart.

A6.text: The first Carl's Jr. restaurants were opened in 1956 in Anaheim and Brea, California.

A7.text: Brothers Richard and Maurice McDonald founded McDonald's in San Bernardino, California, in 1940 as a hamburger stand.

A8.text: The first McDonald's at 1398 North E Street at West 14th Street in San Bernardino, California, on May 15, 1940.
